This probably has to do with felines weird pregnancy ability. You know how common cats give birth to litters and you get very wildly varying fur colors/patterns in the kittens. This is due to each kitten actually having a different father. Cats can get pregnant from multiple males and give birth to kittens for each male. They also seem to be able to hold onto that genetic information and give birth to similar colored/patterned kittens again without that male or a similar one having mated with them for another pregnancy. This is why you can have an all black furred mother cat and all white furred father cat give birth to a striped orange cat.
